[? if young_plan_signatures < 10: The failure of the Young Plan referendum to reach the 10% threshold?][? if young_plan_signatures < 10 and was_in_right_coalition:&nbsp;and?] [? if was_in_right_coalition: Hugenberg's unpopular decision to exit the right-wing coalition exactly a year from now?] and the declining popularity of the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> has convinced the majority of the party to vote out Hugenberg, replacing him with Treviranus, a member of the "Young Conservative" wing of the party. The Young Conservatives are in favor of governmental participation, advancing their goals in the framework of the system. However, the national conservatives retain heavy control over the party and the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> isn't exactly a democratic party yet. [? if stegerwald_path: This leaves the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> as a more nationalistic, conservative alternative to the <span style="color: #000000;">Center</span>. ?]

In response, Hugenberg threatens to take himself and his supporters into a new splinter party, which is unlikely to gain much support, considering he remains deeply unpopular beyond his loyal following.

